cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.DL, cs.HC 

This paper is about testing the performance of major web search engines on navigational queries, which is a topic related to information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) as users described their desired pages, which makes cs.CL a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the study involves human-computer interaction (HCI) as it evaluates the user experience of search engines, which makes cs.HC a possible sub-category. The paper also involves data mining and machine learning techniques to analyze the results, which makes cs.DL a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves web search and web mining, which makes cs.CY a possible sub-category.
